Terms and Conditions for Car Rental Services

These terms and conditions ("Terms") govern the use of car rental services provided by FlexWheels, located at Navrangpura, Ahmedabad, hereinafter referred to as "the Company."

1. Booking and Reservation
1.1. All bookings are subject to availability and confirmation by the Company.
1.2. Customers must provide accurate and complete information at the time of booking, including personal details, contact information, and intended duration of rental.
1.3. The Company reserves the right to refuse any booking at its discretion.

2. Rental Period
2.1. The rental period begins and ends at the times specified in the booking confirmation.
2.2. Extension of the rental period is subject to availability and must be requested in advance. Additional charges may apply for extended rental periods.

3. Payment Terms
3.1. Payment for car rental services must be made in upon vehicle collection, as per the Company's payment policy.
3.2. Accepted payment methods include cash and bank transfers.
3.3. Customers are responsible for any additional charges incurred during the rental period, including fuel, tolls, parking fees, and fines.

4. Cancellation and Refund Policy
4.1. Cancellations must be made at least 1 day before the scheduled pickup time to qualify for a full refund of deposit amount, as per the Company's cancellation policy.
4.2. No-shows or cancellations made after the specified deadline may result in forfeiture of the booking deposit or full payment.

5. Vehicle Usage
5.1. The rented vehicle must only be used for lawful purposes and in accordance with Indian traffic laws and regulations.
5.2. Customers are responsible for any damage, loss, or theft of the rented vehicle during the rental period, excluding normal wear and tear.
5.3. Smoking, carrying pets, and consuming alcohol inside the vehicle are strictly prohibited.

6. Insurance and Liability
6.1. The Company provides basic insurance coverage for rented vehicles, subject to terms and conditions specified in the insurance policy.

7. Maintenance and Breakdown
7.1. The Company ensures that all rented vehicles are well-maintained and in roadworthy condition at the time of rental.
7.2. In case of breakdown or mechanical failure, customers must immediately notify the Company's designated emergency contact and follow instructions provided for assistance.

8. Termination of Rental
8.1. The Company reserves the right to terminate the rental agreement and reclaim the rented vehicle at any time due to violation of these Terms, unsafe driving behavior, or non-payment of fees.
8.2. Customers must return the vehicle to the designated drop-off location at the end of the rental period, failing which additional charges may apply.

9. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
9.1. These Terms and any disputes arising from or related to car rental services provided by the Company shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India.
9.2. Any legal proceedings shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Ahmedabad.
